Lunarpines spark jumped, he was no longer alone in this world he had 
a companion to share it with. For the first time since he'd met the 
Maximals he wasn't thinking about the war, he was thinking about the 
peace. And most of all he was thinking of this sweet inocent shebot 
in his arms. How she got dragged into this chaos was anybodies clue, 
Lunarpine was just glad that she was there.

--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, logomorph@h... wrote:
> ::Shadow Wing::
> 
> She smiled "the only place I'm going is with you my beloved."
> She leaned closer and hugged him again. She was happy just to be 
> close to him.  She felt her spark race as she hugged him.  She 
didn't 
> want to let go of him.  He made her feel complete and knew that her 
> spark was his, totally.
> 
> 
> --- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, cyberwolf4@p... wrote:
> > Lunarpine leaned his head back a little looking a little 
> > confused "Why can't you stay with me, are you going somewhere I 
> > should know about?" he knew what she meant but enjoyed hearing 
her 
> > express herself to him instead of trying to be the strong willed 
> > warrior she wasn't. Shadow Wing was finally becoming comfortable 
> with 
> > him as she was not as what she wanted to be for him.
> >
